		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I had the same problem orbit2002 mentioned in the other thread, after loading my ROM I couldn't figure out how to start the emulation.  But it looked like the emulation window became the blue background color that my ROM uses, so I was a little puzzled why I didn't see any graphics (I'm assuming it did start, and loaded the palette?)<br /><br />Program is looking really great, though!  Definitely has came a long way from the early releases.  I'm pretty much certain I'm gonna start using this, next time I start (or maybe restart) a game project.  I've mostly been doing hardware stuff lately.</div>
<br />
<br />In the toolbar there's a green play-button icon over to the right, with icons that look like a pause icon and green "fast forward" icons with the words "CPU" and "PPU" underneath.  Those are the emulator controls.  I moved them there because I felt it matched the UI experience of other IDEs like Visual Studio where the "run" icon is in the taskbar.
<br />
<br />What ROM are you trying?  
<br />
<br />Thanks for the feedback!

		

